          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Faith is something you understand inherently, though fitting in is new to you. It's not a common stereotype for Jewish boys from Brooklyn to be athletic and sporty, but you were. Your mother wouldn't permit you to try out for football, fearing injury to either your body (on the field) or your soul (off the field and in the comapny of shiksa cheerleaders). So you compromised on track and field, earning varsity your sophomore year and carrying your school to nationals your senior year. Through it all, you struggled with your identity. You were Jewish, you loved being Jewish, you loved everything about being Jewish and didn't seem to have the same problems with your peers when it came to following the laws. The feeling you got when not eating bacon was far superior to the taste of bacon, you believed. This combination of physical prowess and faith earned you the attention of the local Sabbat, whom you discovered when walking through Brooklyn late on Friday night (rather than violate the Shabbos rules by driving home). You thought you were being mugged, something much more meaningful was happening. You still believe the tenets of Judaism, which might be considered heresy by the more hardline Sabbat - but you are wholly willing to accept your legacy as a Cainite, a servant of Shaitan meant to terrify the faithful back into the safety of belief. You have fallen in with Rising Tide because the dynamism of the pack appeals to you (they also needed a priest and are willing to overlook your Brujah blood... for now). However, you sometimes wonder if you would function better in a pack more suited to your personal beliefs. You also struggle with your Humanity. You know you need to eventually get on a Path of Enlightenment, but you need to be careful about which one."
        ],
